---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="CLI Reference"
  description="Complete reference for all shuttle commands, subcommands, and global flags."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    Shuttle is invoked as <code>shuttle &lt;command&gt; [flags]</code>. All commands read
    <code>shuttle.yml</code> from the current directory by default.
  </p>

  <h2>Global flags</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--config &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Path to a specific <code>shuttle.yml</code> file</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--env &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Load <code>shuttle.&lt;name&gt;.yml</code> overlay (or set <code>SHUTTLE_ENV</code>)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--verbose</code></td>
        <td>Enable verbose/debug log output</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Commands</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Command</th>
        <th>Synopsis</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/deploy"><code>deploy</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle deploy [flags]</code></td>
        <td>Build image, transfer to server, run health checks, swap proxy upstream</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/provision"><code>provision</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle provision</code></td>
        <td>Bootstrap a fresh Debian/Ubuntu VPS (Docker, Caddy, deploy user, firewall)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/rollback"><code>rollback</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle rollback [--to &lt;tag&gt;]</code></td>
        <td>Roll back to the previous or a specific deployment</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>destroy</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle destroy</code></td>
        <td>Stop all containers and remove remote app state (irreversible)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>validate</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle validate</code></td>
        <td>Parse and validate <code>shuttle.yml</code> without connecting to any server</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>status</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle status</code></td>
        <td>Show current deployment state (active slot, tag, port, version) per host</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>logs</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle logs [service]</code></td>
        <td>Stream container logs from the remote server via SSH</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>ssh</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle ssh [host]</code></td>
        <td>Open an interactive SSH session to the server</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>exec</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle exec &lt;command&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Run a one-off command in the active container via <code>docker exec</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>lock</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle lock [release]</code></td>
        <td>Inspect or force-release a deploy lock on a host</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/secrets"><code>secrets</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle secrets &lt;set|get|list|remove|push&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Manage AES-256-GCM encrypted secrets</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>license</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle license &lt;validate|info&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Validate or display your Shuttle license key</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/ci"><code>ci</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle ci generate [flags]</code></td>
        <td>Generate GitHub Actions or GitLab CI pipeline configuration</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/dev"><code>dev</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle dev &lt;up|down|restart|logs|status&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Local development environment with Docker Compose and Caddy</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/docs/commands/new"><code>new</code></a></td>
        <td><code>shuttle new [framework] [name]</code></td>
        <td>Scaffold a new project with shuttle.yml, Dockerfile, and services</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>init</code></td>
        <td><code>shuttle init</code></td>
        <td>Create a minimal <code>shuttle.yml</code> in the current directory</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Config file resolution</h2>
  <p>
    Shuttle walks up the directory tree from the current working directory to find
    <code>shuttle.yml</code>. This means you can run <code>shuttle deploy</code> from any
    subdirectory of your project.
  </p>
  <p>
    Environment overlays allow per-environment configuration without duplicating the full file:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">SHUTTLE_ENV=staging shuttle deploy
# Loads shuttle.yml then deep-merges shuttle.staging.yml on top
</code></pre>

  <h2>Exit codes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Code</th>
        <th>Meaning</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>0</code></td>
        <td>Success</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>1</code></td>
        <td>General error (config invalid, deploy failed, SSH error, etc.)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
